Class BaseRegression

  • java.lang.Object
    • magpie.models.BaseModel
      • magpie.models.regression.BaseRegression
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, AbstractRegressionModel, Citable, Commandable, Options, Printable, Savable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractNonlinearRegression, ClassificationRegression, CompositeRegression, LASSORegression, LinearCorrectedRegression, MetallurgicalHeuristicRegression, MixingRuleRegression, MultiObjectiveRegression, PolynomialRegression, RandomGuessRegression, ScikitLearnRegression, SingleGuessRegression, StagedRegression, WekaRegression

    public abstract class BaseRegression
extends BaseModel
implements AbstractRegressionModel
    Base class for all regression models.

    Implemented Commands:

    robust <Q> - Define False Positive Rate used for robust regression. See Motulsky and Brown
    Q: Desired FPR during outlier detection.

      • setRobustRegressionQ

        public void setRobustRegressionQ(double Q)
        Description copied from interface: AbstractRegressionModel
        Set the desired False Discovery Rate for outlier detection. A robust regression parameter of 0.01 is recommended. Zero turns it off. Don't give it less than zero.

        See paper by Benjamini and Hochberg

        Specified by:
        setRobustRegressionQ in interface AbstractRegressionModel
        Parameters:
        Q - Desired FDR
